    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine nostri Domini Jhesu Christi regnante domno nostro <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/21">Berengario</persName>
                        <rs key="#Emperor/king">rege</rs> hic in Italia anno uigisimo tercio sub die
                        secondo de mense augusto indicione tercia decima feliciter. Secundum
                        peticione uestra <persName
                            key="#Coloni/tenants #Conductores #Freeborn #sonOf"><name
                                ref="Landevertus">Landeuertus</name>
                            <rs key="#sonOf">filius</rs></persName> quondam
                                <persName><name>Aziuertus</name></persName>, et <persName
                            key="#Coloni/tenants #Conductores #sonOf"><name ref="Iohannes">Johannes
                                    <rs key="#sonOf">fiulius</rs></name></persName> quondam
                                <persName><name>Isoni de <rs key="#Casalia">casale </rs>Coruulo
                            </name></persName><rs key="#Freeborn">liberis hominibus</rs> locaui
                        uobis ego in Dei nomine <persName key="#Count" ref="#people/166">Anselmus
                            </persName><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/124"><rs
                                key="#Count">comite </rs><rs key="#Comitatus">comitatus</rs>
                            ueronensis</geogName>, idest in integrum <rs key="#Landed_possessions"
                            >ariale </rs>uno una cum <rs key="#Mills">aquimolo</rs> suo juris
                        proprietatis mee quem habere uisus sum, que situs est in <rs key="#Rivers"
                            >fluuio Tartaris</rs> in <rs key="#Ports">porto</rs> de <geogName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Mills #Storage_units #Defensive_elements #Ports"
                                ><placeName
                                key="#Landed_possessions #Mills #Storage_units #Defensive_elements #Ports"
                                ref="#places/572">Rouescello</placeName></geogName> non longe
                            de<orgName key="#Churches">
                            <rs key="#Churches">capella</rs> Sancti Zenonis de eodem <placeName
                                key="#Churches" ref="#places/572">loco
                            Rouescello</placeName></orgName> ab ipso ariale una cum aquimulo, et
                        gresso et regresso suo, ubi dicitur ad <rs key="#Defensive_elements"
                            >fossato</rs>, omnia in integrum uobis locaui, eam uero racione ut super
                        ipso ariale <rs key="#Mills #Privileges #Public_infrastructures">mulino
                            edificare debeatis</rs>, cum <rs key="#Mills #Kilns #Storage_units"
                            >tecto super se habente et rodas et cum uniuersis municionibus et
                            fabrica sua</rs>, que ad ipso molino pertinere dinoscitur, et omnia
                        sicut supra legitur habere, et cum eo fideliter laborare debeatis uos et
                        heredibus uestris <rs key="#Coloni/tenants">libellario nomine ad annos
                            uiginti et nouem</rs>, et exinde reddere debeatis <rs
                            key="#Rent_in_kind">censum</rs> annualiter pro omni festiuitate Sancti
                        Martini quod est de mense november anteposito in ipso anno, nobis et
                        heredibus nostris aut cui nos dederimus <rs key="#Cereals #Maiores #Minores"
                            >anona selg. (<foreign>sic</foreign>) modio uno, segal. modia dua, ordio
                            modio uno, milio modia dua, surico modia dua</rs>, quod faciunt in summa
                        super totum anona modia octo, et ipsa anona infra <rs key="#Castle">castrum,
                            que in suprascripto loco Rouescello constructum fuerit</rs>, dare
                        debeatis et sic [ ] <rs key="#Missus">missum</rs> ipsa anona recepere
                        debead. <rs key="#Exenia">Exenia </rs>uero per annum in ipsa festiuitate
                        Sancti Martini dare debeatis, <rs key="#Poultry">pullo bono uno</rs> caldola
                        una, <rs key="#Wine">uino sectario uno,</rs> aliud uobis [] super imponatur.
                        Proptere(a) spondeo atque repromitto me ego suprascriptus Anselmus [m]eis
                        heredes uobis suprascriptis petitores uel ad uestris heredibus, si de
                        suprascripto ariale et mol[estare ] uos foris excutere, tollere, contendere
                        aut minuare uoluerimus [ ] annos uiginti et nouem, aut aliqua super imposita
                        uobis facere temptauerimus, nisi quod hic superius legitur, et clare factum
                        fuerit, tunc componam ego uel meis her[edibus] uobis uel uestris heredibus
                            <rs key="#Penalty">pena argentum solidos numeratos uiginti et
                        nouem</rs>, et post pena co[ ], hec prensens pagina in eodem statu ut supra
                        legitur firmam et stabilis permaneat usque ad suprascriptos annos uiginti et
                        nouem cum stipulacione subnixa. Acto in <orgName key="#Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/136"><placeName key="#Monasteries"
                                ref="#places/564"><rs key="#Monasteries">monasterio</rs> Sancte
                                Marie sito in Gagio</placeName></orgName> feliciter. Signum + manum
                        superscripti domini <persName key="#Count #Salian" ref="#people/166">Anselmi
                            </persName><rs key="#Count">comitis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Salian">ex franquorum (<foreign>sic</foreign>) genere</rs>, qui
                        hanc pagina fieri rogauit ad omnia superscripta et ei relecta est. Signum
                            <persName key="#Witness #Sculdahis" ref="#people/612">[ ]delmo
                            </persName><rs key="#Sculdahis">sculdasio</rs>
                        <rs key="#Witness">teste</rs>. Signum + + + manibus <persName
                            key="#Witness #sonOf"><name ref="Ausbertus">Auspertus <rs key="#sonOf"
                                    >filius</rs></name></persName>
                        <persName><name ref="Amalbertus">quondam Amelberti</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Witness"><name ref="Plato de Telidiano"
                            >Platone</name></persName> et <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Iohannes de Telidiano">Johanne <placeName ref="#places/595">de
                                    Telidiano</placeName>
                                <rs key="#sonOf">filius</rs></name></persName>
                        <persName><name ref="Giselbertus">quondam Giseluerti</name></persName>, et
                                <persName><name ref="Lupus">Lupo <rs key="#sonOf">fiulius</rs>
                            </name></persName>
                        <persName><name ref="Teudebertus de Rouescello">quondam Teudibertus
                            </name></persName><placeName ref="#places/572">de Rouescello</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Witness">testes</rs>. Signum + manu <persName
                            key="#Salian #sonOf #vassusOf"><name ref="Iso">Isoni <rs key="#Salian"
                                    >ex franquorum genere</rs>
                                <rs key="#vassusOf">uasso</rs></name></persName>
                        <persName key="#seniorOf"><name ref="Amizo">Amizoni</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Witness">teste</rs>. Signum + manu <persName key="#Witness #sonOf"
                                ><name ref="Teudo">Teudoni</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#sonOf">fiulius</rs>
                        <persName><name ref="Odelbertus">quondam Odelberti</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Witness">teste</rs>. + Ego <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Madelbertus">Madelbertus </name></persName>rogatus <rs
                            key="#Witness">testis</rs> manu mea subscripsi. + Ego <persName
                            key="#Notary" ref="#people/611">Pedelbertus <rs key="#Notary"
                                >notarius</rs></persName> rogatus manu mea qui hanc paginam scripsi,
                        et post tradita complevi. </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="editions">
                <p>Fainelli, CDV, II, n. 95, pp. 122-124.</p>
            </div>
